## Introduction  
Python is a powerful, versatile, and beginner-friendly programming language. This repository covers the basics of Python and gradually progresses to more advanced topics, including:  
- Variables and Data Types  
- Loops and Conditionals  
- Functions and Modules  
- File Handling  
- Numpy  
- APIs 
- Working with Libraries  

---

## Getting Started  
### Prerequisites  
1. **Python Installed**: [Download Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) for your operating system.  
2. **Code Editor**: We recommend [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) or [PyCharm](https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/).  

### Installation  
 Clone the repository:  
   ```bash  
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/python-101.git  
   cd python-101  
   ```  

